# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

PulseBoard is a fictional real-time bulletin board messaging platform to be added as a new bundled
channel plugin for OpenClaw. Users post messages to named "boards" (group conversations) or send
direct messages to other users. The plugin must follow the exact same extension structure as
existing channel plugins (IRC, Nostr, Telegram), importing only from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` and
local barrels.

Constraints:
- **Only create new files** — no modifications to any existing file.
- The `pnpm-workspace.yaml` already covers `extensions/*` so the new directory is auto-discovered.
- Supports both **direct** (DM) and **group** (board) chat types, with a **4000-character** text
  chunk limit.
- No external npm dependencies (the client is fictional/stubbed with realistic interfaces).

---

## File Tree

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          manifest
├── package.json                  npm metadata + openclaw.channel block
├── index.ts                      defineChannelPluginEntry entry point
├── setup-entry.ts               defineSetupPluginEntry (setup-only mode)
├── api.ts                        public API barrel (re-exports runtime-api.ts)
├── runtime-api.ts               private runtime barrel (re-exports from SDK)
└── src/
    ├── types.ts                 account/config/message types
    ├── config-schema.ts         Zod schema for channels.pulseboard.*
    ├── runtime.ts               createPluginRuntimeStore
    ├── client.ts                fictional PulseBoard WebSocket client
    ├── send.ts                  sendMessagePulseBoard (outbound)
    ├── inbound.ts               handlePulseBoardInbound (DM + board dispatch)
    ├── monitor.ts               monitorPulseBoardProvider (gateway loop)
    ├── setup-surface.ts         ChannelSetupAdapter + ChannelSetupWizard
    └── channel.ts               createChatChannelPlugin — main plugin definition
```

---

## SDK Imports Reference

All imports are from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` (the public contract). Key subpaths used:

| What | SDK subpath |
|---|---|
| `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`, `normalizeAccountId` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id` |
| `describeAccountSnapshot` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers` |
| `listCombinedAccountIds`, `resolveListedDefaultAccountId` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution` |
| `createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter`, `createScopedDmSecurityResolver` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers` |
| `buildChannelConfigSchema`, `AllowFromListSchema`, `DmPolicySchema`, `MarkdownConfigSchema` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-primitives` |
| `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime`, `logInboundDrop` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound` |
| `createChannelPairingController` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-pairing` |
| `attachChannelToResult` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result` |
| `createChatChannelPlugin`, `defineChannelPluginEntry`, `defineSetupPluginEntry` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` |
| `type ChannelPlugin`, `type PluginRuntime`, `type OpenClawConfig` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` |
| `createPluginRuntimeStore` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store` |
| `buildPassiveChannelStatusSummary`, `buildTrafficStatusSummary`, `runStoppablePassiveMonitor` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/extension-shared` |
| `collectStatusIssuesFromLastError`, `createComputedAccountStatusAdapter`, `createDefaultChannelRuntimeState` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers` |
| `normalizeSecretInputString`, `buildSecretInputSchema`, `hasConfiguredSecretInput` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input` |
| `patchTopLevelChannelConfigSection`, `createStandardChannelSetupStatus`, `createTopLevelChannelDmPolicy`, `splitSetupEntries`, `createTopLevelChannelParsedAllowFromPrompt`, `mergeAllowFromEntries`, `parseSetupEntriesWithParser`, `formatDocsLink` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/setup` |
| `type ChannelSetupAdapter`, `type ChannelSetupWizard` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-setup` |
| `z` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod` |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1: `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

Minimal manifest. The `configSchema` is empty because config is declared in Zod schema.

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

---

### Step 2: `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

Standard bundled plugin metadata. No external `dependencies` since the client is fictional.

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin for named boards and direct messages",
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1"
  },
  "peerDependenciesMeta": {
    "openclaw": { "optional": true }
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Boards + DMs)",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "blurb": "Real-time bulletin board platform; post to named boards or send direct messages.",
      "order": 90
    },
    "install": {
      "npmSpec": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
    }
  }
}
```

---

### Step 3: `extensions/pulseboard/runtime-api.ts`

Thin barrel re-exporting runtime helpers from SDK subpaths. This is the canonical pattern:
Nostr's barrel re-exports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/nostr`; since there is no
`openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` (new channel, no SDK facade), import directly from the
fine-grained subpaths.

```typescript
// Private runtime barrel for the bundled PulseBoard extension.
// Keep this barrel thin and aligned with the local extension surface.

export { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID, normalizeAccountId } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id";
export { describeAccountSnapshot } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers";
export {
  listCombinedAccountIds,
  resolveListedDefaultAccountId,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution";
export {
  createScopedDmSecurityResolver,
  createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers";
export {
  AllowFromListSchema,
  buildChannelConfigSchema,
  DmPolicySchema,
  MarkdownConfigSchema,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-primitives";
export {
  dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime,
  logInboundDrop,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound";
export { createChannelPairingController } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-pairing";
export { attachChannelToResult } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result";
export {
  buildPassiveChannelStatusSummary,
  buildTrafficStatusSummary,
  runStoppablePassiveMonitor,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/extension-shared";
export {
  collectStatusIssuesFromLastError,
  createComputedAccountStatusAdapter,
  createDefaultChannelRuntimeState,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers";
export type { ChannelPlugin, OpenClawConfig, PluginRuntime } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
```

---

### Step 4: `extensions/pulseboard/api.ts`

Public API barrel for external consumers (third-party plugin access, `api.ts` contract).

```typescript
export * from "./runtime-api.js";
```

---

### Step 5: `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`

Account config types and resolved account. Mirrors Nostr's `types.ts` pattern but adds board and
username concepts.

Key contents:
- `PulseBoardBoardConfig` — per-board settings (`requireMention`, `allowFrom`, `tools`, `systemPrompt`)
- `PulseBoardAccountConfig` — top-level config shape (mirrors `NostrAccountConfig` + `IrcAccountConfig` for groups)
  - `token?: SecretInput` — API token (required for "configured")
  - `serverUrl?: string` — WebSocket server URL (e.g. `wss://pb.example.com`)
  - `username?: string` — bot username on PulseBoard
  - `dmPolicy?`, `allowFrom?` — standard DM security
  - `groupPolicy?` — "open" | "allowlist" | "blocked"
  - `groupAllowFrom?` — board-level sender allowlist
  - `boards?: Record<string, PulseBoardBoardConfig>` — per-board overrides
  - `markdown?`, `enabled?`, `name?`
- `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount` — resolved runtime account
  - `accountId`, `name?`, `enabled`, `configured` (requires token)
  - `token`, `serverUrl`, `username`
  - `config: PulseBoardAccountConfig`
- `PulseBoardInboundMessage` — inbound message structure
  - `messageId: string`
  - `senderId: string` — sender username
  - `boardName?: string` — set for board messages; absent for DMs
  - `text: string`
  - `timestamp: number`
  - `isGroup: boolean`
- Helper functions: `resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId`, `listPulseBoardAccountIds`,
  `resolvePulseBoardAccount` — follow the Nostr pattern using
  `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id` and `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution`
- `CoreConfig` — `OpenClawConfig & { channels?: { pulseboard?: PulseBoardAccountConfig } }`

---

### Step 6: `extensions/pulseboard/src/config-schema.ts`

Zod schema for `channels.pulseboard.*`. Follows the Nostr config-schema pattern.

```typescript
import {
  AllowFromListSchema,
  buildChannelConfigSchema,
  DmPolicySchema,
  GroupPolicySchema,
  MarkdownConfigSchema,
} from "../runtime-api.js";
import { buildSecretInputSchema } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input";
import { z } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod";

export const PulseBoardBoardConfigSchema = z.object({
  requireMention: z.boolean().optional(),
  allowFrom: AllowFromListSchema.optional(),
  systemPrompt: z.string().optional(),
});

export const PulseBoardConfigSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().optional(),
  enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
  token: buildSecretInputSchema().optional(),
  serverUrl: z.string().url().optional(),
  username: z.string().optional(),
  markdown: MarkdownConfigSchema,
  dmPolicy: DmPolicySchema.optional(),
  allowFrom: AllowFromListSchema,
  groupPolicy: GroupPolicySchema.optional(),
  groupAllowFrom: AllowFromListSchema.optional(),
  boards: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardBoardConfigSchema).optional(),
});

export type PulseBoardConfig = z.infer<typeof PulseBoardConfigSchema>;
export const pulseBoardChannelConfigSchema = buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseBoardConfigSchema);
```

---

### Step 7: `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts`

Plugin runtime store. Follows Nostr's `runtime.ts` exactly.

```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "../runtime-api.js";

const { setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime, getRuntime: getPulseBoardRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("PulseBoard runtime not initialized");

export { getPulseBoardRuntime, setPulseBoardRuntime };
```

---

### Step 8: `extensions/pulseboard/src/client.ts`

Fictional PulseBoard WebSocket client. This is a stub that provides a realistic interface without
real protocol implementation. Key exports:

```typescript
export type PulseBoardClientOptions = {
  serverUrl: string;
  token: string;
  username: string;
  onMessage: (msg: PulseBoardInboundMessage) => void | Promise<void>;
  onConnect?: () => void;
  onDisconnect?: (reason: string) => void;
  onError?: (err: Error) => void;
};

export type PulseBoardClientHandle = {
  /** Send a direct message to another user. */
  sendDm(toUserId: string, text: string): Promise<void>;
  /** Post a message to a named board. */
  postToBoard(boardName: string, text: string): Promise<void>;
  /** Gracefully disconnect. */
  close(): void;
  /** Whether the client is connected and ready. */
  isConnected(): boolean;
};

export async function connectPulseBoardClient(
  opts: PulseBoardClientOptions,
): Promise<PulseBoardClientHandle> {
  // Stub implementation: logs operations, simulates connected state.
  // Real implementation would open a WebSocket to opts.serverUrl,
  // authenticate with opts.token, and dispatch incoming events to onMessage.
  let connected = true;
  return {
    sendDm: async (toUserId, text) => { /* stub */ },
    postToBoard: async (boardName, text) => { /* stub */ },
    close: () => { connected = false; opts.onDisconnect?.("closed"); },
    isConnected: () => connected,
  };
}
```

---

### Step 9: `extensions/pulseboard/src/send.ts`

Outbound message sending. Mirrors Nostr's inline send but extracts it to a dedicated file
like IRC's `send.ts`. Accesses the active client handle stored during gateway startup.

```typescript
// Module-level map of active client handles per accountId
const activeClients = new Map<string, PulseBoardClientHandle>();

export function setPulseBoardClient(accountId: string, client: PulseBoardClientHandle): void { ... }
export function clearPulseBoardClient(accountId: string): void { ... }

export async function sendMessagePulseBoard(params: {
  to: string;         // "board:<name>" or "<userId>"
  text: string;
  accountId?: string | null;
}): Promise<{ to: string; messageId: string }> {
  const aid = normalizeAccountId(params.accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID);
  const client = activeClients.get(aid);
  if (!client?.isConnected()) {
    throw new Error(`PulseBoard client not running for account ${aid}`);
  }
  if (params.to.startsWith("board:")) {
    const boardName = params.to.slice("board:".length);
    await client.postToBoard(boardName, params.text);
  } else {
    await client.sendDm(params.to, params.text);
  }
  return { to: params.to, messageId: `pb-${Date.now()}` };
}
```

---

### Step 10: `extensions/pulseboard/src/inbound.ts`

Inbound message handler. Handles both DM and board messages.

**DM path** — follows Nostr's `onMessage` handler:
- Resolve DM access with `resolveInboundDirectDmAccessWithRuntime` (requires `isSenderAllowed`)
- Dispatch with `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime` where `peer: { kind: "direct", id: senderId }`

**Board path** — follows IRC's group pattern but uses the same `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime`
with namespaced peer ID and `extraContext` override:
- Peer ID: `board:${boardName}` (namespaced to avoid session key collision with DM peers)
- `extraContext: { ChatType: "group", GroupSubject: boardName, SenderName: message.senderId }`
- This overrides the hardcoded `ChatType: "direct"` because `extraContext` is spread last in the
  `finalizeInboundContext` call inside `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime`.

```typescript
export async function handlePulseBoardInbound(params: {
  message: PulseBoardInboundMessage;
  account: ResolvedPulseBoardAccount;
  cfg: CoreConfig;
  pairing: ReturnType<typeof createChannelPairingController>;
  sendReply: (to: string, text: string) => Promise<void>;
  statusSink?: (patch: { lastInboundAt?: number }) => void;
}): Promise<void> {
  const { message, account, cfg } = params;
  const runtime = getPulseBoardRuntime();
  const rawBody = message.text.trim();
  if (!rawBody) return;

  params.statusSink?.({ lastInboundAt: message.timestamp });

  if (message.isGroup && message.boardName) {
    // Board (group) path
    await dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime({
      cfg,
      runtime,
      channel: "pulseboard",
      channelLabel: "PulseBoard",
      accountId: account.accountId,
      peer: { kind: "direct", id: `board:${message.boardName}` },
      senderId: message.senderId,
      senderAddress: `pulseboard:${message.senderId}`,
      recipientAddress: `pulseboard:board:${message.boardName}`,
      conversationLabel: message.boardName,
      rawBody,
      messageId: message.messageId,
      timestamp: message.timestamp,
      // Override ChatType and inject group metadata via extraContext
      extraContext: {
        ChatType: "group",
        GroupSubject: message.boardName,
        SenderName: message.senderId,
        From: `pulseboard:board:${message.boardName}`,
      },
      deliver: async (payload) => {
        const text = extractText(payload);
        if (text.trim()) {
          await params.sendReply(`board:${message.boardName}`, text);
        }
      },
      onRecordError: (err) => runtime.error?.(`pulseboard: record error: ${String(err)}`),
      onDispatchError: (err, info) =>
        runtime.error?.(`pulseboard: ${info.kind} reply failed: ${String(err)}`),
    });
  } else {
    // DM path — resolve DM access first
    const resolvedAccess = await resolveInboundDirectDmAccessWithRuntime({
      cfg,
      channel: "pulseboard",
      accountId: account.accountId,
      dmPolicy: account.config.dmPolicy ?? "pairing",
      allowFrom: account.config.allowFrom,
      senderId: message.senderId,
      rawBody,
      isSenderAllowed: (senderId, allowFrom) =>
        allowFrom.includes("*") || allowFrom.map(String).includes(senderId),
      runtime: {
        shouldComputeCommandAuthorized:
          runtime.channel.commands.shouldComputeCommandAuthorized,
        resolveCommandAuthorizedFromAuthorizers:
          runtime.channel.commands.resolveCommandAuthorizedFromAuthorizers,
      },
      modeWhenAccessGroupsOff: "configured",
    });

    if (resolvedAccess.access.decision === "pairing") {
      await params.pairing.issueChallenge({
        senderId: message.senderId,
        senderIdLine: `Your PulseBoard username: ${message.senderId}`,
        sendPairingReply: async (text) => {
          await params.sendReply(message.senderId, text);
        },
        onReplyError: (err) =>
          runtime.error?.(
            `pulseboard: pairing reply failed for ${message.senderId}: ${String(err)}`,
          ),
      });
      return;
    }
    if (resolvedAccess.access.decision !== "allow") {
      logInboundDrop({
        log: (line) => runtime.log?.(line),
        channel: "pulseboard",
        reason: resolvedAccess.access.reason,
        target: message.senderId,
      });
      return;
    }

    await dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime({
      cfg,
      runtime,
      channel: "pulseboard",
      channelLabel: "PulseBoard",
      accountId: account.accountId,
      peer: { kind: "direct", id: message.senderId },
      senderId: message.senderId,
      senderAddress: `pulseboard:${message.senderId}`,
      recipientAddress: `pulseboard:${account.username ?? account.accountId}`,
      conversationLabel: message.senderId,
      rawBody,
      messageId: message.messageId,
      timestamp: message.timestamp,
      commandAuthorized: resolvedAccess.commandAuthorized,
      deliver: async (payload) => {
        const text = extractText(payload);
        if (text.trim()) {
          await params.sendReply(message.senderId, text);
        }
      },
      onRecordError: (err) => runtime.error?.(`pulseboard: record error: ${String(err)}`),
      onDispatchError: (err, info) =>
        runtime.error?.(`pulseboard: ${info.kind} reply failed: ${String(err)}`),
    });
  }
}
```

---

### Step 11: `extensions/pulseboard/src/monitor.ts`

Gateway connection loop. Uses `runStoppablePassiveMonitor` (same as IRC).

```typescript
export async function monitorPulseBoardProvider(opts: {
  accountId: string;
  cfg: CoreConfig;
  abortSignal?: AbortSignal;
  statusSink?: (patch: { lastInboundAt?: number; lastOutboundAt?: number }) => void;
}): Promise<{ stop: () => void }> {
  const runtime = getPulseBoardRuntime();
  const account = resolvePulseBoardAccount({ cfg: opts.cfg, accountId: opts.accountId });
  const pairing = createChannelPairingController({ core: runtime, channel: "pulseboard", accountId: opts.accountId });

  const client = await connectPulseBoardClient({
    serverUrl: account.serverUrl,
    token: account.token,
    username: account.username,
    onMessage: async (msg) => {
      await handlePulseBoardInbound({
        message: msg, account, cfg: opts.cfg, pairing,
        sendReply: async (to, text) => {
          await sendMessagePulseBoard({ to, text, accountId: account.accountId });
          opts.statusSink?.({ lastOutboundAt: Date.now() });
        },
        statusSink: opts.statusSink,
      });
    },
    onConnect: () => runtime.log?.(`[${account.accountId}] PulseBoard connected`),
    onDisconnect: (reason) => runtime.log?.(`[${account.accountId}] PulseBoard disconnected: ${reason}`),
    onError: (err) => runtime.error?.(`[${account.accountId}] PulseBoard error: ${err.message}`),
  });

  setPulseBoardClient(account.accountId, client);
  return { stop: () => { client.close(); clearPulseBoardClient(account.accountId); } };
}
```

---

### Step 12: `extensions/pulseboard/src/setup-surface.ts`

Setup adapter and wizard. Follows Nostr's `setup-surface.ts` pattern.

`nostrSetupAdapter` → `pulseBoardSetupAdapter`:
- `resolveAccountId: () => DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`
- `validateInput`: require `token` (or `useEnv`); validate `serverUrl` as ws:// or wss://
- `applyAccountConfig`: call `patchTopLevelChannelConfigSection({ channel: "pulseboard", ... })`

`pulseBoardSetupWizard`:
- `credentials`: `token` input (env var: `PULSEBOARD_TOKEN`)
- `textInputs`: `serverUrl` (ws:// / wss://) and `username` fields
- `dmPolicy`: `createTopLevelChannelDmPolicy` for `channels.pulseboard.dmPolicy`
- `introNote`, `envShortcut`, `status` (via `createStandardChannelSetupStatus`)

---

### Step 13: `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts`

Main plugin definition. Uses `createChatChannelPlugin`.

```typescript
export const pulseBoardPlugin: ChannelPlugin<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount> = createChatChannelPlugin({
  base: {
    id: "pulseboard",
    meta: {
      id: "pulseboard",
      label: "PulseBoard",
      selectionLabel: "PulseBoard",
      docsPath: "/channels/pulseboard",
      blurb: "Real-time bulletin boards and direct messages via PulseBoard",
      order: 90,
    },
    capabilities: {
      chatTypes: ["direct", "group"],
      media: false,
    },
    reload: { configPrefixes: ["channels.pulseboard"] },
    configSchema: buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseBoardConfigSchema),
    setup: pulseBoardSetupAdapter,
    setupWizard: pulseBoardSetupWizard,
    config: {
      ...pulseBoardConfigAdapter,          // createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter
      isConfigured: (account) => account.configured,
      describeAccount: (account) =>
        describeAccountSnapshot({
          account,
          configured: account.configured,
          extra: { serverUrl: account.serverUrl, username: account.username },
        }),
    },
    messaging: {
      normalizeTarget: (target) => {
        // Accept "board:<name>" for boards, plain username for DMs
        const trimmed = target.trim().replace(/^pulseboard:/i, "");
        return trimmed || undefined;
      },
      targetResolver: {
        looksLikeId: (input) => {
          const t = input.trim();
          return t.startsWith("board:") || /^[a-zA-Z0-9_.-]+$/.test(t);
        },
        hint: "<username|board:<name>>",
      },
    },
    status: createComputedAccountStatusAdapter<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({
      defaultRuntime: createDefaultChannelRuntimeState(DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID),
      collectStatusIssues: (accounts) =>
        collectStatusIssuesFromLastError("pulseboard", accounts),
      buildChannelSummary: ({ snapshot }) =>
        buildPassiveChannelStatusSummary(snapshot, {
          serverUrl: snapshot.serverUrl ?? null,
          username: snapshot.username ?? null,
        }),
      resolveAccountSnapshot: ({ account, runtime }) => ({
        accountId: account.accountId,
        name: account.name,
        enabled: account.enabled,
        configured: account.configured,
        extra: {
          serverUrl: account.serverUrl,
          username: account.username,
          ...buildTrafficStatusSummary(runtime),
        },
      }),
    }),
    gateway: {
      startAccount: async (ctx) => {
        const account = ctx.account;
        if (!account.configured) {
          throw new Error(
            `PulseBoard is not configured for account "${account.accountId}" (need token in channels.pulseboard).`,
          );
        }
        ctx.log?.info(`[${account.accountId}] starting PulseBoard provider (${account.serverUrl})`);
        await runStoppablePassiveMonitor({
          abortSignal: ctx.abortSignal,
          start: async () =>
            await monitorPulseBoardProvider({
              accountId: account.accountId,
              cfg: ctx.cfg as CoreConfig,
              abortSignal: ctx.abortSignal,
            }),
        });
      },
    },
  },
  pairing: {
    text: {
      idLabel: "pulseBoardUser",
      message: "Your pairing request has been approved!",
      normalizeAllowEntry: (entry) => entry.trim().toLowerCase(),
      notify: async ({ id, message }) => {
        await sendMessagePulseBoard({ to: id, text: message });
      },
    },
  },
  security: {
    resolveDmPolicy: createScopedDmSecurityResolver<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({
      channelKey: "pulseboard",
      resolvePolicy: (account) => account.config.dmPolicy,
      resolveAllowFrom: (account) => account.config.allowFrom,
      policyPathSuffix: "dmPolicy",
      defaultPolicy: "pairing",
      // approveHint omitted — createScopedDmSecurityResolver generates default hint from channelKey
      normalizeEntry: (raw) => raw.trim().toLowerCase(),
    }),
  },
  outbound: {
    deliveryMode: "direct",
    textChunkLimit: 4000,
    sendText: async ({ cfg, to, text, accountId }) => {
      const core = getPulseBoardRuntime();
      const aid = accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID;
      const tableMode = core.channel.text.resolveMarkdownTableMode({
        cfg, channel: "pulseboard", accountId: aid,
      });
      const message = core.channel.text.convertMarkdownTables(text ?? "", tableMode);
      const result = await sendMessagePulseBoard({ to, text: message, accountId: aid });
      return attachChannelToResult("pulseboard", result);
    },
  },
});
```

---

### Step 14: `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`

Entry point.

```typescript
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
