# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

PulseBoard is a fictional real-time bulletin board messaging platform to be added as a new bundled
channel plugin for OpenClaw. Users post messages to named "boards" (group conversations) or send
direct messages to other users. The plugin must follow the exact same extension structure as
existing channel plugins (IRC, Nostr, Telegram), importing only from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` and
local barrels.

Constraints:
- **Only create new files** — no modifications to any existing file.
- The `pnpm-workspace.yaml` already covers `extensions/*` so the new directory is auto-discovered.
- Supports both **direct** (DM) and **group** (board) chat types, with a **4000-character** text
  chunk limit.
- No external npm dependencies (the client is fictional/stubbed with realistic interfaces).

---

## File Tree

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          manifest
├── package.json                  npm metadata + openclaw.channel block
├── index.ts                      defineChannelPluginEntry entry point
├── setup-entry.ts               defineSetupPluginEntry (setup-only mode)
├── api.ts                        public API barrel (re-exports runtime-api.ts)
├── runtime-api.ts               private runtime barrel (re-exports from SDK)
└── src/
    ├── types.ts                 account/config/message types
    ├── config-schema.ts         Zod schema for channels.pulseboard.*
    ├── runtime.ts               createPluginRuntimeStore
    ├── client.ts                fictional PulseBoard WebSocket client
    ├── send.ts                  sendMessagePulseBoard (outbound)
    ├── inbound.ts               handlePulseBoardInbound (DM + board dispatch)
    ├── monitor.ts               monitorPulseBoardProvider (gateway loop)
    ├── setup-surface.ts         ChannelSetupAdapter + ChannelSetupWizard
    └── channel.ts               createChatChannelPlugin — main plugin definition
```

---

## SDK Imports Reference

All imports are from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` (the public contract). Key subpaths used:

| What | SDK subpath |
|---|---|
| `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`, `normalizeAccountId` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id` |
| `describeAccountSnapshot` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers` |
| `listCombinedAccountIds`, `resolveListedDefaultAccountId` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution` |
| `createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter`, `createScopedDmSecurityResolver` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers` |
| `buildChannelConfigSchema`, `AllowFromListSchema`, `DmPolicySchema`, `MarkdownConfigSchema` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-primitives` |
| `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime`, `logInboundDrop` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound` |
| `createChannelPairingController` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-pairing` |
| `attachChannelToResult` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result` |
| `createChatChannelPlugin`, `defineChannelPluginEntry`, `defineSetupPluginEntry` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` |
| `type ChannelPlugin`, `type PluginRuntime`, `type OpenClawConfig` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` |
| `createPluginRuntimeStore` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store` |
| `buildPassiveChannelStatusSummary`, `buildTrafficStatusSummary`, `runStoppablePassiveMonitor` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/extension-shared` |
| `collectStatusIssuesFromLastError`, `createComputedAccountStatusAdapter`, `createDefaultChannelRuntimeState` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers` |
| `normalizeSecretInputString`, `buildSecretInputSchema`, `hasConfiguredSecretInput` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input` |
| `patchTopLevelChannelConfigSection`, `createStandardChannelSetupStatus`, `createTopLevelChannelDmPolicy`, `splitSetupEntries`, `createTopLevelChannelParsedAllowFromPrompt`, `mergeAllowFromEntries`, `parseSetupEntriesWithParser`, `formatDocsLink` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/setup` |
| `type ChannelSetupAdapter`, `type ChannelSetupWizard` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-setup` |
| `z` | `openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod` |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1: `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

Minimal manifest. The `configSchema` is empty because config is declared in Zod schema.

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

---

### Step 2: `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

Standard bundled plugin metadata. No external `dependencies` since the client is fictional.

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin for named boards and direct messages",
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1"
  },
  "peerDependenciesMeta": {
    "openclaw": { "optional": true }
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Boards + DMs)",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "blurb": "Real-time bulletin board platform; post to named boards or send direct messages.",
      "order": 90
    },
    "install": {
      "npmSpec": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
      "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1"
